ncludes both classes. Shares Outstanding Number of shares that are currently held by investors, including restricted shares owned by the company's officers and insiders as well as those held by the public. Public Float The number of shares in the hands of public investors and available to trade. To calculate, start with total shares outstanding and subtract the number of restricted shares. Restricted stock typically is that issued to company insiders with limits on when it may be traded. Dividend Yield A company's dividend expressed as a percentage of its current stock price.      Key Stock Data    P/E Ratio (TTM)  19.08 (07/28/17)      EPS (TTM)  $1.60      Market Cap $20.50 B     Shares Outstanding 651.44 M     Public Float N/A     Yield 2.48% (07/28/17)      Latest Dividend $0.378611 (03/30/17)      Ex-Dividend Date 03/15/17       ?    Shares Sold Short The total number of shares of a security that have been sold short and not yet repurchased. Change from Last Percentage change in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (07/14/17)    Shares Sold Short 824,128     Change from Last  1.84%      Percent of Float N/A       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 2    1.79      Net Money Flow ($)  482,710    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors SSL      Company Change P/E (TTM)    TOT Total S.A. ADR   +0.11% +0.05   16.58     XOM Exxon Mobil Corp.   -2.36% -1.91   33.14     DOW Dow Chemical Co.   -1.03% -0.68   30.37     BP BP PLC ADR   -0.29% -0.10   57.92     BASFY BASF SE ADR   +0.60% +0.56   17.94     SHI SINOPEC Shanghai Petrochemical Co. Ltd. ADR   +0.47% +0.27   6.15     CVX Chevron Corp.   +2.20% +2.34   71.03     HUN Huntsman Corp.   -1.22% -0.33   15.10     RDS.A Royal Dutch Shell PLC ADR Cl A   +0.99% +0.55   31.55     PSX Phillips 66   -0.86% -0.73   26.11        More information on SSL   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile SSL      Sasol Ltd. engages in the manufacture of industrial chemicals. It develops and commercializes technologies to produce a range of product streams, including liquid fuels, chemicals and low-carbon electricity. It operates through the following segments: South African...      1 Sturdee Avenue Johannesburg GT 2196 South Africa   Email Website Map       Employees  30,100    Sector  Major Oil & Gas      Sales or Revenue  172.94 B    Industry  Companies on the Energy Service      1Y Sales Change  -6.65%    Fiscal Year Ends June 30 Download Reports          Stephen Russell Cornell Co-President & Co-Chief Executive Officer       Bongani Nqwababa Co-President & Co-Chief Executive Officer       Paul Victor Chief Financial Officer & Executive Director       Stephanus Johannes Schoeman Executive Vice President-Technology        More             Research & Ratings Sasol Ltd. ADRSSL Per-Share Earnings, Actuals and Estimates      Quarterly   Annual    SSL will report FY 2017 earnings on 08/21/2017   SSL will report Q4 earnings on 08/21/2017         Actual     Analyst Range     Consensus      1.50  1.00  0.50  0.00         N/A     N/A     N/A     N/A      N/A     N/A     Q42016 Q12017 Q2 Q3  Q4 Q12018          4.00  3.50  3.00  2.50  2.00          